    },
    {
      "topic": "The Myth of JEE and Entrance Examinations",
      "speaker": "Guest",
      "text": "When JEE is mentioned, we feel proud saying it's the world's toughest exam. But if you look deeper, this is the only race where we're running alone and we've self-proclaimed ourselves as the best. No other country boasts about their entrance exams like this. If JEE is truly the best exam, then the top engineers from IIT should be winning the ICPC competition globally. But they're not. This shows that entrance exams don't necessarily produce the best engineers. The real issue is the pressure and false narrative we've created around JEE."
